    "name": "Kansas City Original Sound",
    "profile": "One of the groups that favored a soul-meets-hip-hop approach was [a=Kansas City Original Sound].  In 1995, the group, then known as K-OS (Kansas City Original Sound), appeared to land a deal with RCA on the strength of a super-hot demo anchored by the single [m367334], but before the album's release, the label restructured, leaving K-OS without a deal.   The debut album, [m813692], provided R&B for a hip-hop generation with up-tempo funk selections as well as romantic ballads and slow jams. The album turned out to be Kansas City Original Sound's only album. Marlon Hatcher and Keith Murrell went on to record with R. Kelly and release an album on Interscope Records under the name [a=Talent].\r\n\r\n",
